article.headline: Wis-Green Bay 76, FDU 67
article.story: HACKENSACK, N.J. (AP) -- Josh Lawrence and Mike Schachtner scored 19 points apiece to lead Wisconsin-Green Bay to a 76-67 win over Fairleigh Dickinson on Tuesday night. Ryan Evanochko added 15 points for the Phoenix (2-4), and Ryan Werch also finished in double figures with 11 points. Andre Harris led Fairleigh Dickinson (2-2) with 15 points. Wisconsin-Green Bay scored the first five points of the game and shot 52 percent in the first half to take a 39-32 halftime lead. The Phoenix increased the lead to 42-32 on a 3-pointer by Troy Cotton in the opening minute of the second half. FDU then ran off 14 straight points, capped by a Jordan Ingram layup, to take a 46-42 lead with 12:48 to play. But Lawrence keyed a Wisconsin-Green Bay rally, scoring all eight points in an 8-2 run to give the Phoenix a 50-48 lead with 10:55 to play. FDU tied the score at 54 on a layup by Michael Peeples, but a 3-pointer by Schachtner put the Phoenix ahead for good with 7:25 left. Wisconsin-Green Bay stretched the lead to as many as 14 points late in the game.
